node.text: Collaborated with @Qualcomm for this Mobile Photography Tutorial! Shot on the #Snapdragon 888 5G Mobile Platform! Check out @SnapdragonInsiders for more pro-quality #ShotOnSnapdragon photos [ad]

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of mountain, sky and nature.

node.text: One of the best mountain views ever. It’s evenings like this that you’ll never forget

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Lake Tahoe. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text: This place has some of the most beautiful and perfect water you’ll ever see. Last summer I visited Lake Tahoe 3-4 times and had the time of my life. Wish I could’ve made it back this year

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text: Here’s a shot from a recent heli flight over Washington and the Cascade Mountains. We saw a hot air balloon floating over Rainier as we headed back to Seattle. Definitely got super lucky. Check out my story for the raw photo and video flying past the balloon. Forgive me for the quality 😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text: Cabin at the very top of the world 👀 Insane to think that they actually built this lookout at the very top of a pinnacle. I can’t even imagine what the process was like

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Wyoming. May be an image of nature and road.

node.text: Wyoming - definitely one of the wildest places out there 🤠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington. May be an image of sky, nature and mountain.

node.text: Mountain layers from a distance. Recently took this from the top of a mountain. The hike up was easily one of the hardest I’ve done. Views like this make me feel like it was worth it 😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington with @kierra_summer, and @wildlilyindex. May be an image of standing, outdoors, tree and twilight.

node.text: Whimsical cabin stays at @wildlilyindex 🏡 Definitely one of my favorites so far. Perfect for those nearby hikes and forest explorations with friends 😌

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Eastern Sierra Mountains with @kyleresatka. May be an image of nature and lake.

node.text: One of the best lakes out there. These peaks reminded me of something you’d find in another country, yet this place was once only a short drive away

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Oregon. May be an image of bird, nature and body of water.

node.text: Caught a photo of this bald eagle at sunrise 🦅 If you zoom in on its talons you can tell that it just caught breakfast 🐟 Crazy to seeing moments like this in the Northwest

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii. May be an image of nature and mountain.

node.text: Flying through an ancient crater that created one of these islands was truly an experience I will never forget. The views were out of this world 🚁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in American Southwest with @angelaliggs. May be an image of twilight and nature.

node.text: Walking on a dream at sunrise ✨ Definitely one of the more magical mornings I’ve had where this entire reflection was a palette for creative ideas

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Hawaiian sunrise vibes for the win 🏝 The combination of these unique mountains and amazing water colors made for a pallet that blew me away. These islands have so much to offer
